    "alt": null
  }), mdx("p", null, "People, real-world people - in the world - buy themselves a webizen, or in fact - they might even want to buy a few, but after they\u2019ve bought their webizen it is their webizen, their property it is owned by them.\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "Designed to serve and support the needs of their owners; both online in the infosphere and as a consequence of how it is our world has been made to function - it works to help people in the real-world too.\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "In our world of \u2018Artificial Intelligence\u2019 and problems with our \u2018rule of law\u2019, we are now unprotected in \u2018the metaverse\u2019.\xA0 Webizen are being designed to become a class of new products to help humans."), mdx("p", null, "Webizen: Describes a 'Citizen of the Web'. A Webizen is a person who is adept in Web techniques and who essentially lives on the Web. \xA0 They are different from natural persons or legal persons (companies); Webizen are \u2018Web Persons\u2019\u2026"), mdx("p", null, "The Webizen Project is about providing for natural people, support for peace & natural justice; by working to provide some tools they may need to keep themselves safe; in this ever increasing world of hostility, violence & mutability of access to justice & truth telling support, for natural persons."), mdx("p", null, "The project is about the creation & design of what many describe as \u2018artificial minds\u2019 or in-effect; new species of Artificial \u2018entities\u2019, \u2018things\u2019; that have historically, only really been produced to consume us; now, we seek to provide - a different class of computing software, a class of software agents that are designed to serve & protect us."), mdx("p", null, "Index"), mdx("p", null, mdx("a", {
