    "alt": null
  }), mdx("p", null, "When defining Webizen - I want to consider: The Code of Chivalry - Forming an AI Lore of Chivalry\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "The Three Laws of Robotics;"), mdx("p", null, "Was first published in 1942 by Isaac Asimov , the concept therefore pre-dates the 1945 post war article by Vannaver Bush on \u2018As We May Think\u2019."), mdx("p", null, "First Law:\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "A robot may not injure a human being or, through inaction, allow a human being to come to harm."), mdx("p", null, "Second Law:\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "A robot must obey the orders given it by human beings except where such orders would conflict with the First Law."), mdx("p", null, "Third Law:\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "A robot must protect its own existence as long as such protection does not conflict with the First or Second Law."), mdx("h3", {
    "id": "what-other-rules-need-to-be-defined"
  }, "What other Rules need to be defined?"), mdx("p", null, "Considerations include;"), mdx("ol", null, mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
  }, "It has an owner: it serves its owner(s).")), mdx("ol", null, mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
  }, "They probably need to be defined in a way that supports the ability for a family to have many different webizen running on the same \u2018webizen box\u2019; but if there\u2019s a change (family separation, or child becomes an adult) their \u2018webizen\u2019 can be migrated."), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
  }, "If the owner is a child or is otherwise similarly incapable of \u2018personhood\u2019, then it shall be subject to the rules defined by that persons guardian & the \u2018webizen rules\u2019.")), mdx("ol", {
    "start": 3
  }, mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
  }, "Cannot Fabricate \u2018evidence\u2019, that there must be an ability to audit the logical basis of bot facts"), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
  }, "Defining the rules of \u2018Battle Bots\u2019; what is allowed in the civilian domain and what is not allowed?\xA0\xA0"), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
  }, "How are rules defined to ensure the people, webizen serve are protected from acts of violence, harms, threats, etc..\xA0")), mdx("h3", {
    "id": "webizen-ethics-cont"
  }, "Webizen Ethics (cont)."), mdx("p", null, "There are also significant ideological considerations that do need to be made; about the difference between designing a \u2018thing\u2019 that is a tool; and that the responsibility over how it is designed to operate by its owner, is really up to that person - which is in-turn, a morality related method; that seeks to support \u2018personal responsibility\u2019 rather than \u2018big brother\u2019 or \u2018system defined rules\u2019 of conduct.\xA0 This methodology; is in-turn, a bit like providing other types of tools, whether it be desktop computers or applications that work on them, like spreadsheet programs; or physical artefacts, like cars or hammers; all of which, can be used for harmful / wrongful purposes; But that there\u2019s either no controls, or limited controls placed upon the sale of these \u2018products\u2019.\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "In effect a design method; to support the notion, that \u201CThe primary person responsible for ones behaviour is themselves\u2026\u201D... \xA0 Therein - design standards would in-turn seek to ensure that the natural persons who owns their \u2018webizen\u2019 (environment); is supported, in seeking to ensure that they are indeed, responsible for the actions of their webizen.\xA0 This would include an array of design qualities & requirements; to ensure this form of ideology is indeed supported; whilst also offering a capacity for innovators to innovate."), mdx("p", null, "But the consequence, much like cars or hammers - is that people might seek to use them as a weapon; as such, there are various considerations to be made about how best to address this problem, perhaps not so much in relation to the \u2018webizen\u2019 tooling itself; but moreover, how it is designed to be supported by broader ecosystems - including but not limited to, law & legal processes."), mdx("p", null, "Yet - these considerations are not intended to entirely absolve responsibility for ensuring good design.\xA0 Part of the \u2018webizen.org\u2019 initiative, is to figure out how to form a multi-stakeholder approach to forming \u2018open standards\u2019 that support and are in-turn supported by participants who get involved."), mdx("p", null, "There are various methods to seek to provide hygiene and ensure that \u2018webizen systems\u2019 are safe and indeed also; very secure (technically).\xA0\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "It is considered that a \u2018webizen\u2019 be a far more complicated form of \u2018identity apparatus\u2019 or tooling; which is very different to the present-day mainstream \u2018beliefs\u2019 about the benefits for mankind by issuing them \u2018wallets\u2019 powered by \u2018web3\u2019 with keys / credentials, that can be reissued in the case the wallet is lost.\xA0\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "This isn\u2019t just about \u2018wallets\u2019, its moreover about human agency - and the need to produce a solution, despite the consequences of decisions made by others to not provide infrastructure online to support human agency (ie: my old \u2018knowledge banking\u2019 works); by refactoring the designs, to better consider / take into account; the circumstances where the primary goals relate to \u2018property\u2019 (inclusive to AI / Information Infrastructure) & contract law.\xA0\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "The outcome of producing Webizen, should result in significant \u2018safety / dignity\u2019 improvements for the people who are able to buy one, and have it help them with their life as influenced via technology.\xA0 Part of how this will be achieved is via \u2018safety protocols\u2019 (per below, but think - star-trek, holodeck - which has safety protocols); therein, some of what needs to be done, is a bunch of work on various forms of values frameworks that need to be produced as ontologies, so that owners can decide which \u2018optional\u2019 ones they want to employ\u2019 whilst, the product may not function if the mandatory ones are not \u2018turned on\u2019 or in some way otherwise corrupted (aka safety protocols)."), mdx("h2", {
    "id": "classes-of-webizen"
  }, "CLASSES OF WEBIZEN"), mdx("p", null, "The concept of a \u2018webizen\u2019 is intended to be about \u2018helper\u2019 robots, sometimes described as \u2018side-kicks\u2019, \u2018assistants\u2019 or similar.\xA0 Part of the objective is to support the preservation of freedom of thought for natural persons, as is an instrumental foundation required for any form of #HumanRights\n", mdx("img", {
